# **Overview** {#overview}

This document contains references and guidelines for IOT AYO API Services. This API allows IOT Camera middleware in venue partners to integrate their system into AYO. 

# **Host** {#host}

Below is the host for an API:

| URL | Usage |
| :---- | :---- |
| https://iot-api.ayo.co.id/api/v1/ | AYO API Production URL |
| http://iot-api.ayodev.xyz:6060/api/v1 | AYO API Development URL |

 

# **Authentication** {#authentication}

In order to use the API, you will need a fulfillment service ID, such as a ***venue code***, an ***API token***, and a ***Venue secret key***. AYO will provide you access to the keys for each venue.

* **Venue Code:** is a 10-character unique code for each venue registered with AYO which is automatically generated by the AYO system.  
* **API Token**: The API token/key is a unique code that functions to provide login access and connect code from one developer to another. As already explained, the API key is helpful in the authentication process when the API is executed.  
* **Venue Secret Key:** The secret key to generating signatures on each request.  
* **Signature:** A mechanism to ensure that the data in each request and response cannot be hijacked by unauthorized users. This signature is generated using the SHA512-HMAC algorithm.  
* **HMAC**: an acronym for Hash-based message authentication, which is a mechanism for calculating message authentication codes. It involves a cryptographic hash function combined with a secret key. Just like the name, HMAC's purpose is to authenticate messages.

# **Signature** {#signature}

To secure the data sent between the AYO system and middleware services, we use a signature mechanism for every request. This is intended so that data sent through the AYO system to middlewares or vice versa is properly maintained and prevents data manipulation by unauthorized parties. We use HMAC with SHA512 as the algorithm to generate the request signature. Here is the step on how we generate the signature:

**Example Request Body:**

| {    "token": "3qUFjksFEG8U5Xi5aXF2lY2WT8jYRDYCFerLmHjWILrawiVpeyjm0OV6tQrl",    "booking\_id": "BK/0042/230228/0000118",    "field\_name": "Lapangan Utama",    "date": "2023-03-04",    "start\_time": "12:00:00",    "end\_time": "14:00:00",    "total\_price": 2800000} |
| :---- |

1. **Sorting the data by key in ascending order:**

| {    "booking\_id": "BK/0042/230228/0000118",    "date": "2023-03-04",    "end\_time": "14:00:00",    "field\_name": "Lapangan Utama",    "start\_time": "12:00:00",    "token": "3qUFjksFEG8U5Xi5aXF2lY2WT8jYRDYCFerLmHjWILrawiVpeyjm0OV6tQrl",    "total\_price": 2800000} |
| :---- |

2. **Convert the sorted data to Query String:**

| booking\_id\=BK%2F0042%2F230228%2F0000118&date\=2023-03-04&end\_time\=14%3A00%3A00&field\_name\=Lapangan+Utama&start\_time\=12%3A00%3A00&token\=3qUFjksFEG8U5Xi5aXF2lY2WT8jYRDYCFerLmHjWILrawiVpeyjm0OV6tQrl&total\_price\=2800000 |
| :---- |

3. **Prepare the Private/Secret Key:**

| lM8ZgVG73FK6GY49YWIm4pPWSXR8qsuzBHPPRa0N6D6NTir8FbCmiy8ROFZoqrvoIaIcyoT69AqChRlE4UpaoHzhPjFgV4vDKoIZNtfp3PXK4wDUdlbrd0RKFsfKprM89ldEXKL8ruLmPDEpPXKEjEHuFGSGANcRS3Pt8BUx1nZmnJoP8wtkRpfqkxbXFet |
| :---- |

4. **Generating the Signature (PHP):**

| \<?php$signature \= hash\_hmac('sha512', $data, $privateKey); |
| :---- |

5. **Signature result:**

| 87592e1033c0fc65767ead30b02aca0002f0e43ebb3904b3689dbed8a2033b6a09234ebde2536b0a9de495ea0c48265be768eda2684f9e1f0f211add51c839a3 |
| :---- |

6. **To verify the generated signature is correct, please check it on an online signature generator such as [https://hmacgenerator.com/](https://hmacgenerator.com/) or a similar tool.**

# **Request Headers** {#request-headers}

Please send mandatory headers for every request as in the example below:

| Key | Value | Description |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Accept | application/json | Accepting requests as the JSON |
| Content-Type | application/json | Content request as the JSON |

# **API Resources** {#api-resources}

1. ## **Get Watermark** {#get-watermark}

**Request Method**:	 **GET**

**API Endpoint**:		**API-BASE-URL**/watermark

**Interval Suggestion: 	Every 24 hours**

**Body Request (Payload)**

| Field | Mandatory | Format | Description |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | ----- |
| token | Yes | String | API token |
| signature | Yes | HMAC | Hash HMAC with SHA512 |
| venue\_code | Yes | String | This will be automatically generated from the AYO system. |

## 

**Example Request:**

| curl \--location POST 'https://iot-api.ayo.co.id/v1/watermark?token=xxxx\&venue\_code=yyyy\&signature=123423532435' |
| :---- |

**Example Response:**

| {  "error": false,  "status\_code": 200,  "data": \[    {      "resolution": "480",      "path": "[https://asset.ayo.co.id/venue-a-watermark-480.png](https://asset.ayo.co.id/venue-a-watermark-380.png)",      },      {      "resolution": "720",      "path": "[https://asset.ayo.co.id/venue-a-watermark-720.png](https://asset.ayo.co.id/venue-a-watermark-380.png)",      },      {      "resolution": "1080",      "path": "[https://asset.ayo.co.id/venue-a-watermark-1080.png](https://asset.ayo.co.id/venue-a-watermark-380.png)",      },    ...  \],} |
| :---- |

3. ## **Save Video Available** {#save-video-available}

**Request Method**:	 **POST**

**API Endpoint**:		**API-BASE-URL**/save-video-available

**Interval Suggestion: 	After video available to purchase**

**Body Request (Payload)**

| Field | Mandatory | Format | Description |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | ----- |
| token | Yes | String | API token |
| signature | Yes | HMAC | Hash HMAC with SHA512 |
| booking\_id | Yes | String | This will be automatically generated from the AYO system. |
| type | Yes | String | Type of video (full/clip) |
| preview\_path | Yes | String | Path of Preview Video (16:9 mp4) |
| image\_path | Yes | String | Path of Preview image (16:9 still png) |
| start\_timestamp | Yes | ISO8601 Datetime | Start datetime of the video, example: (2018-04-01T15:20:15+07:00) |
| end\_timestamp | Yes | ISO8601 Datetime | End datetime of the video,  example: (2018-04-01T15:20:15+07:00) |
| unique\_id | Yes | String | Unique ID of video generated by middleware (will be used in Get Video Request API) |
| venue\_code | Yes | String |  |

## 

**Example Request:**

| curl \--location POST 'https://iot-api.ayo.co.id/v1/save-video-available' \\ \--header 'Accept: application/json' \\ \--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\ \--data-raw '{     "token": "12132435",     "signature": "22e8cb57b51ddae4a7f8520c523a47ebaa6c21f9f5ff6f7bad19090d2cf96c8f8f003093b18b3bad9ac2a576a2827e96cf3805d7a02c38d99a9c83851653694a",     "booking\_id": "BX/20230406/001",     "type": "clip",     "preview\_path": "https://asset.ayo.co.id/apng-preview-123456.mp4",     "image\_path": "https://asset.ayo.co.id/png-preview-123456.png",     "unique\_id": "XXXYSFEADAFEEB",     "start\_timestamp": "2025-04-01T15:20:15+07:00",     "end\_timestamp": "2025-04-01T15:22:15+07:00",     "venue\_code": "12345" } ' |
| :---- |

**Example Response:**

| {   "error": false,   "message": "Video Preview saved",   "status\_code": 200 } |
| :---- |

5. ## **Save Video/Clip Path** {#save-video/clip-path}

**Request Method**:	 **POST**

**API Endpoint**:		**API-BASE-URL**/save-video

**Interval Suggestion: 	Based on Get Request API data response**

**Body Request (Payload)**

| Field | Mandatory | Format | Description |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | ----- |
| token | Yes | String | API token |
| signature | Yes | HMAC | Hash HMAC with SHA512 |
| venue\_code | Yes | String | This will be automatically generated from the AYO system. |
| video\_request\_id | Yes | String | Video Request ID from Get Video Request API |
| booking\_id | Yes | String | This will be automatically generated from the AYO system. |
| type | Yes | String | Type of video (full/clip) |
| video | Yes | Array of Object | Refer to **Video Parameter Request**  |
| start\_timestamp | Yes | ISO8601 Datetime | Start datetime of the video, example: (2018-04-01T15:20:15+07:00) |
| end\_timestamp | Yes | ISO8601 Datetime | End datetime of the video,  example: (2018-04-01T15:20:15+07:00) |

## 

**Video Parameter Request (Payload)**

| Field | Mandatory | Format | Description |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | ----- |
| stream\_path | Yes | String | Path of Stream video in R2 (m3u8) |
| download\_path | Yes | String | Path of mp4 video in R2 |
| resolution | Yes | String | Resolution of the video (480/720/1080) |

## 

**Example Request:**

| curl \--location POST 'https://iot-api.ayo.co.id/v1/save-video' \\ \--header 'Accept: application/json' \\ \--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\ \--data-raw '{     "video\_request\_id": "faegeag232",     "token": "3qUFjksFEG8U5Xi5aXF2lY2WT8jYRDYCFerLmHjWILrawiVpeyjm0OV6tQrl",     "signature": "22e8cb57b51ddae4a7f8520c523a47ebaa6c21f9f5ff6f7bad19090d2cf96c8f8f003093b18b3bad9ac2a576a2827e96cf3805d7a02c38d99a9c83851653694a",     "booking\_id": "BX/20230406/001",     "type": "clip",     "video": \[         {             "stream\_path": "https://asset.ayo.co.id/test-video-123456-720.m3u8",             "download\_path": "https://asset.ayo.co.id/test-video-123456-720.mp4",             "resolution": "720"         },         {             "stream\_path": "https://asset.ayo.co.id/test-video-123456-1080.m3u8",             "download\_path": "https://asset.ayo.co.id/test-video-123456-1080.mp4",             "resolution": "1080"         }     \],     "start\_timestamp": "2025-04-01T15:20:15+07:00",     "end\_timestamp": "2025-04-01T15:22:15+07:00" } ' |
| :---- |

**Example Response:**

| {   "error": false,   "message": "Video path saved",   "status\_code": 200 } |
| :---- |

# **HTTP Status Codes** {#http-status-codes}

Here are the list codes.

| HTTP Code | Error Message | Description |
| :---: | :---- | :---- |
| **400** | Bad Request | The request parameter(s) are not valid |
| **403** | Invalid Signature | The signature value is not valid for the body request. |
| **403** | Unauthenticated: Invalid token | The token is not valid or the AYO system cannot verify the token. |
| **200** | Success | The request was successful. |
| **500** | Server Error | There was an error on the server during the processing of the request |
